  "prompt": "How old do you have to be to qualify for AARP membership?",
  "response": "As of October 2023, you must be **50 years old** or older to qualify for AARP membership. AARP (formerly the American Association of Retired Persons) offers a wide range of benefits and services tailored to individuals in this age group, including:\n\n- **Health and Wellness Programs:** Access to health insurance options, prescription discounts, and wellness resources.\n- **Financial Tools:** Resources for retirement planning, investment advice, and loans with favorable terms.\n- **Travel Discounts:** Special rates on hotels, car rentals, and vacation packages.\n- **Entertainment and Leisure:** Discounts on tickets for events, restaurants, and various leisure activities.\n- **Advocacy:** Representation on issues affecting older adults at local, state, and national levels.\n\nMembership also includes access to publications like the AARP Magazine, providing information on topics relevant to members. Additionally, family members (spouses) can often join at a reduced rate.\n\nIf you're interested in joining, you can sign up through the [AARP website](https://www.aarp.org/) or by contacting their customer service for more information on membership options and benefits.",
